strings.Value: "I was hoping you'd remain outside — must I kill you to keep you from hounding me?"
"You and your master will find I'm full of surprises."
"I'll get your master even if I have to fight my way through the Hell, Abaddon, and the Abyss to reach him."
"Jubilost."
"Octavia."
"Regongar."
"Ekundayo."
"Valerie."
"Jaethal."
"...Nok-Nok."
"Harrim."
"Amiri."
"Linzi."
"Tristian."
"Kaessi."
"I'm imprrressed, {race}... You still brrreathe!"
"So deterrrmined! Such pathos! Who are you trrrying to imprrress with this false brrravado, {race}?"
"Don't count on that, {race}. Don't count on that."
"So rrrude and so self-rrrighteous! But wherrre is the confidence behind this show of courrrage?"
"I'll rrrememberrr yourrr name."
"You want to know my name, crow? I'm Jubilost Narthropple, so fly along and inform your dim-witted master that the greatest explorer of {g|Golarion}Golarion{/g} honors his shabby den with a visit!"
"I'll tell! My name is Octavia, I am {mf|baron's|baroness's} friend, and your master will regret it when he stands before us at last."
"I'm not afraid of you or this 'Vordakai'. I am Regongar. I'll carve it on your master's forehead so he doesn't forget."
"Ekundayo. I never deny my enemies the right to know my name."
"How much longer are you going to bother me, bird? I'm Jaethal. Take my name and choke on it. Show yourself again, you'll regret it!"
"Dispense with your mockery, raven. I am Valerie, loyal companion of the {mf|baron|baroness} and {mf|his|her} protector. Now leave us."

"Yourrr companions, perrrhaps?" {n}The raven croaks spitefully.{/n} "Just send them home, be they not prrreparrred to meet Doom itself!" {n}The raven caws a few times, then settles on its perch.{/n} "Orrr maybe therrre's a trrrue herrro among them, one who'd agrrree to follow you into the jaws of death? Come, tell me who!"

"I want a closerrr look at those who followed you to the sanctuarrry of my masterrr." {n}The raven's eyes flit across your allies.{/n} "Let's starrrt with the perrrson closest to you — which of yourrr band has the honorrr of being yourrr dearrrest frrriend?"
"Do you fearrr to be shamed in the eyes of yourrr accomplices? Which of yourrr band do you fearrr to disappoint most?"
"Don't keep my masterrr waiting."
